Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:03.53,Default,,0,0,0,,(this White Dragon) was declared a 5 Sou by Akagi Shigeru when he decared Ron
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.96,0:00:08.93,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a reason that isn't such a wild guess
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.73,0:00:11.93,Default,,0,0,0,,You can read it off the discards
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.86,0:00:14.86,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a reading?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.86,0:00:16.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't you remember?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.86,0:00:18.63,Default,,0,0,0,,In South round 1
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.63,0:00:20.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Harada's hand
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.30,0:00:23.46,Default,,0,0,0,,oh, yes
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.20,0:00:27.36,Default,,0,0,0,,he declared Riichi on the 11th turn by discarding a 4 Sou (bamboo)
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.36,0:00:32.23,Default,,0,0,0,,But in the end he didn't draw his tile.\NThe hand ended as a draw with Harada still in Tenpai
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.23,0:00:37.03,Default,,0,0,0,,After the draw, his open hand showed he had 3 dora, a Mangan.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.03,0:00:39.03,Default,,0,0,0,,A 7 Sou edge wait
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.56,0:00:46.56,Default,,0,0,0,,When you saw that hand, did anything cross your mind?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.93,0:00:49.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Just for a moment I thought...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.93,0:00:51.93,Default,,0,0,0,,discarding the 4 Sou to declare Riichi...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.93,0:00:53.93,Default,,0,0,0,,that was very strange
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.93,0:00:55.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Keeping the 4 Sou...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.93,0:00:57.93,Default,,0,0,0,,and instead discarding the 8 Sou
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.93,0:01:00.43,Default,,0,0,0,,then the 5 Sou wait would give an {\b1\i1}Ittsu{\b0\i0} with 3 Dora
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.43,0:01:02.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Mangan without declaring Riichi
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.43,0:01:05.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Clearly discarding the 5 Sou bothered him
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.96,0:01:08.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Didn't it, though
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.03,0:01:12.30,Default,,0,0,0,,throwing away a qualifying Yaku to instead declare Riichi
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.30,0:01:15.70,Default,,0,0,0,,A most unlikely way to play
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.70,0:01:19.96,Default,,0,0,0,,The reason why Harada played the way he did,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.96,0:01:23.70,Default,,0,0,0,,is he decided the chance of the Ittsu wait was extremely slim
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.13,0:01:28.00,Default,,0,0,0,,At that time
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.00,0:01:30.00,Default,,0,0,0,,perhaps, in Soga's hand...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.00,0:01:32.06,Default,,0,0,0,,There might have been a few 5 Sou
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.26,0:01:35.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Naturally, he provided that information to Harada
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.93,0:01:36.96,Default,,0,0,0,,he had that advantage
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.96,0:01:39.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I suppose that Harada just might also have known...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.86,0:01:43.80,Default,,0,0,0,,that there weren't four 5 Sou tiles
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.80,0:01:48.56,Default,,0,0,0,,that in total, there were only 3...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.50,0:01:54.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Open the box
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.46,0:01:59.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Do it
