Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.36,0:03:06.36,Default - white,,0,0,0,,{\pos(428,407)}Episode 7
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.36,0:03:06.36,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(432,297.667)}Ten: Tenho-doori no Kaidanji\N(Nice guy on the path of Tenho)
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.20,0:03:21.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Well then...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.16,0:03:42.88,Default,,0,0,0,,As we expected, there's a fourth 5 tile inside
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.94,0:03:46.20,Default,,0,0,0,,If so, it's in there.\NThere's a 5 Sou (bamboo)!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.23,0:04:02.23,Default,,0,0,0,,And the last one...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.60,0:04:04.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Okaay. Enough already
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.76,0:04:06.76,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a 5 Pin there
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.76,0:04:11.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Akagi was also waiting on a 5 Pin
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.66,0:04:15.96,Default,,0,0,0,,That 5 Pin alone is enough. Case closed
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.96,0:04:18.46,Default,,0,0,0,,B-but...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.56,0:04:18.56,Default,,0,0,0,,T-the FUCK?!?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.06,0:04:20.06,Default,,0,0,0,,The last one
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.06,0:04:23.20,Default,,0,0,0,,the sole remaining tile
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.16,0:04:28.96,Default,,0,0,0,,HUNH?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.76,0:04:39.50,Default,,0,0,0,,He got it wrong!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.50,0:04:41.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Akagi got it wrong!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.90,0:04:45.73,Default,,0,0,0,,No
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.73,0:04:50.90,Default,,0,0,0,,His reading was flawless
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.90,0:04:52.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Because Harada himself...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.90,0:04:54.90,Default,,0,0,0,,wanted to give it up half way through
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.20,0:05:01.10,Default,,0,0,0,,That last tile
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.10,0:05:04.50,Default,,0,0,0,,it really {\b1\i1}ought{\b0\i0} to have been a 5 sou
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.68,0:05:08.20,Default,,0,0,0,,but in actuality it was 5 MAN
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.34,0:05:13.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Harada had ordered the 5 Sou and 5 Pin swapped with White Dragons
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.96,0:05:18.36,Default,,0,0,0,,but his underling mistook the order, not using a 5 Sou
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.36,0:05:21.76,Default,,0,0,0,,instead swapping a 5 Man
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.76,0:05:28.90,Default,,0,0,0,,A mistake like that, there's no way to predict it
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.90,0:05:31.63,Default,,0,0,0,,B-but it doesn't matter!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.63,0:05:34.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Akagi was in fact waiting on a 5 Pin as well!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.40,0:05:39.33,Default,,0,0,0,,The win is confirmed. Harada said it himself!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.33,0:05:44.93,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't matter. Akagi's win is complete!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.93,0:05:48.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay. Enough already!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.90,0:05:52.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Harada said it himself! Akagi has survived
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.66,0:06:01.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Hiroyuki...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.90,0:06:03.90,Default,,0,0,0,,It's all one
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.86,0:06:09.20,Default,,0,0,0,,What Harada says has nothing to do with it
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.20,0:06:13.73,Default,,0,0,0,,I declared a Ron on a 5 Sou\NAnd the missing tile wasn't a 5 Sou
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.73,0:06:17.33,Default,,0,0,0,,To me, the result is all that matters
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.30,0:06:26.43,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't need it. Winning like that
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.43,0:06:28.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Akagi!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.60,0:06:34.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Harada
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.13,0:06:38.66,Default,,0,0,0,,It's been a while since I've been here
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.66,0:06:41.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Was fun
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.43,0:06:57.50,Default,,0,0,0,,A most interesting man
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.15,0:07:00.15,Default,,0,0,0,,But no one is in Tenpai!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.05,0:07:03.35,Default,,0,0,0,,The contest isn't over yet
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.35,0:07:05.65,Default,,0,0,0,,The day of the final will be changed
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.65,0:07:09.25,Default,,0,0,0,,and the rules revised
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.25,0:07:12.58,Default,,0,0,0,,both teams can suggest new ones
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.55,0:07:16.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Agreed
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.21,0:09:00.21,Default,,0,0,0,,For all of us, after all this,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.21,0:09:03.38,Default,,0,0,0,,What in the world becomes of us?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.35,0:09:08.51,Default,,0,0,0,,As I'm a human being I will perish
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.51,0:09:10.98,Default,,0,0,0,,and return to the earth
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.98,0:09:13.85,Default,,0,0,0,,And then, after how many thousands of years,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.85,0:09:18.55,Default,,0,0,0,,we're reborn as something else
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.55,0:09:21.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe as microbes spread throughout in the sea
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.45,0:09:25.08,Default,,0,0,0,,to be eaten by some faggy fish
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.08,0:09:28.31,Default,,0,0,0,,or maybe as some whelp,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.31,0:09:30.31,Default,,0,0,0,,or a bird
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.48,0:09:34.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't really care when I die
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.78,0:09:38.68,Default,,0,0,0,,because life is reborn
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.65,0:09:42.65,Default,,0,0,0,,but the one thing that bothers me
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.65,0:09:46.91,Default,,0,0,0,,when I, as a human being, drop dead
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.91,0:09:51.61,Default,,0,0,0,,is this feeling of {\b1\i1}who I am{\b0\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.61,0:09:55.38,Default,,0,0,0,,that consciousness will vanish
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.38,0:09:58.25,Default,,0,0,0,,What really scares me
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.25,0:10:02.38,Default,,0,0,0,,is becoming what I'm not
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.35,0:10:06.35,Default,,0,0,0,,And for that, I'm sorry
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.35,0:10:09.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you understand?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.71,0:10:17.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Should I win,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.35,0:10:19.05,Default,,0,0,0,,or should I fail,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.05,0:10:21.58,Default,,0,0,0,,It's {\b1\i1}Akagi Shigeru{\b0\i0} who won...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.58,0:10:23.58,Default,,0,0,0,,or lost
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.78,0:10:28.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Whatever Harada does is of no consquence
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.55,0:10:31.71,Default,,0,0,0,,I decided that tile was a 5 Sou
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.71,0:10:35.51,Default,,0,0,0,,and the tile itself wasn't a 5 Sou
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.51,0:10:39.38,Default,,0,0,0,,that's the sole thing that's important
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.35,0:10:43.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Ten,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.78,0:10:55.21,Default,,0,0,0,,It's up to you now
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.88,0:11:15.35,Default - white,,0,0,0,,{\pos(428.8,382.865)}Day of the East/West Final
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.45,0:11:20.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Ten,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.58,0:11:22.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Can I ask you something?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.91,0:11:27.25,Default,,0,0,0,,If it had been you,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.25,0:11:30.85,Default,,0,0,0,,would you have done the same as Akagi?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.68,0:11:38.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I remain
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.25,0:11:42.31,Default,,0,0,0,,because if you don't remain, you can't win
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.31,0:11:44.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Remain
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.41,0:11:51.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm me. You're you.\NAkagi is Akagi.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.98,0:11:55.75,Default,,0,0,0,,No one lives the same
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.75,0:11:57.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Here and now,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.75,0:12:02.45,Default,,0,0,0,,you and I have survived this far
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.45,0:12:04.45,Default,,0,0,0,,and that is everything
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.81,0:12:10.15,Default,,0,0,0,,And what's more
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.15,0:12:13.21,Default,,0,0,0,,I, above all else,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.21,0:12:17.45,Default,,0,0,0,,concentrate wholeheartedly on victory
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.05,0:12:22.25,Default,,0,0,0,,and to that end I'll suggest a certain rule to the West team
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.25,0:12:32.85,Default,,0,0,0,,a rule which can best play to your logical nature
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.68,0:12:38.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Ten, we've been waiting for you.\NThis way please
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.85,0:12:48.48,Default,,0,0,0,,"Clear" Mahjong?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.48,0:12:50.48,Default,,0,0,0,,What is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.05,0:12:55.15,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a Mahjong team variant that does without trading points
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.15,0:13:02.08,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a rule which awards victory to the team who clears 5 agreed upon Yaku
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.08,0:13:04.75,Default,,0,0,0,,The Yaku one must clear...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.75,0:13:07.21,Default,,0,0,0,,are certain 2 Han Yaku
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.21,0:13:11.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Ittsu, Sansyoku, Chanta, Chtoitsu, SanAnKou
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.58,0:13:13.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Calling tiles is allowed
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.31,0:13:15.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you joking?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.75,0:13:19.05,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no reason why we have to agree to a foolish game like that!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.05,0:13:21.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Quiet!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.35,0:13:27.21,Default,,0,0,0,,It's fine. We agree
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.48,0:13:31.48,Default,,0,0,0,,And your side?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.48,0:13:34.41,Default,,0,0,0,,The normal point system,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.41,0:13:37.81,Default,,0,0,0,,If a member goes bankrupt, that team loses.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.81,0:13:41.55,Default,,0,0,0,,So it's not just pure luck
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.11,0:13:44.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, then
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.11,0:13:47.75,Default,,0,0,0,,You're okay playing with both these rules together?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.08,0:13:51.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Fine
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.95,0:13:55.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Proposing an idiotic rule like that
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.95,0:13:59.48,Default,,0,0,0,,is proof enough they're cornered
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.75,0:15:36.48,Default,,0,0,0,,The Yaku which must be cleared...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.48,0:15:38.48,Default,,0,0,0,,can largely be separated into two groups
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.08,0:15:44.01,Default,,0,0,0,,the first group, because it's a team game, offers protection against direct hits
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.01,0:15:48.08,Default,,0,0,0,,they are mobile, quick Yaku for which you can call tiles
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.08,0:15:53.45,Default,,0,0,0,,these are Ittsu, Sansyoku, and Chanta
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.45,0:15:54.65,Default,,0,0,0,,And on the other hand...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.65,0:15:58.35,Default,,0,0,0,,there are laborious Yaku which you must construct on your own
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.35,0:16:01.51,Default,,0,0,0,,namely, Chitoitsu and SanAnKou
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.51,0:16:06.08,Default,,0,0,0,,specifically, of all five, SanAnKou is the biggest hurdle
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.08,0:16:08.68,Default,,0,0,0,,You might say it has the number one level of difficulty
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.85,0:17:02.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Pon
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.31,0:17:11.05,Default,,0,0,0,,A single suit hand？
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.72,0:17:25.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Kan
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.38,0:17:42.26,Default,,0,0,0,,The South team knows full well that SanAnKou is the key to Clear Mahjong.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.26,0:17:44.14,Default,,0,0,0,,So If I declare a closed Kan,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.14,0:17:48.08,Default,,0,0,0,,to the contrary, they ought to imagine I don't see the true worth a SanAnKou
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.24,0:18:06.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Soga's going for a Chinisou?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.15,0:18:09.02,Default,,0,0,0,,But if I declare a 2nd closed Kan
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.02,0:18:11.92,Default,,0,0,0,,as you'd expect, they'll perceive I'm aiming for a SanAnKou
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.20,0:18:19.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Chii
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.65,0:18:45.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Got it!\NA confirmed SanAnKou
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.05,0:18:51.75,Default,,0,0,0,,There's only two 3 Sou tiles left
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.15,0:18:53.91,Default,,0,0,0,,a terrible wait,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.91,0:18:56.15,Default,,0,0,0,,but if Hiroyuki has a 3 Sou
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.15,0:18:58.78,Default,,0,0,0,,and deals it into my hand,\Nmy SanAnKou is complete
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.11,0:19:09.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Hiroyuki,\NDo you have any 3 Sou?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.08,0:19:13.45,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't have any
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.58,0:19:16.98,Default,,0,0,0,,What Sou tiles do you have?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.95,0:19:22.21,Default,,0,0,0,,5 Sou, 7 Sou, 9 Sou
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.01,0:19:25.01,Default,,0,0,0,,After that, 1 Man
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.01,0:19:27.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Can he deal into my hand at all?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.15,0:19:29.58,Default,,0,0,0,,As far as that's concerned
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.58,0:19:32.25,Default,,0,0,0,,there's merely two tiles left on this 3/6 wait
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.25,0:19:34.95,Default,,0,0,0,,just waiting for a win is almost impossible
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.48,0:19:42.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Without doubt he's got a Sou (Bamboo) single suit hand
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.55,0:19:46.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyone can clearly see this from his two exposed calls
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.28,0:19:49.51,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a danger he's on a 4 or 5 Sou double sided wait
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.51,0:19:51.35,Default,,0,0,0,,HOWEVER
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.35,0:19:54.28,Default,,0,0,0,,this is the path I must take
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.48,0:20:20.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Chi
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.65,0:20:32.48,Default,,0,0,0,,If I deal into his hand the risk of a foolish Haneman or Baiman hit is huge
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.48,0:20:34.45,Default,,0,0,0,,HOWEVER
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.45,0:20:37.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Risk and Return are two sides of the same coin
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.45,0:20:39.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Into the jet black darkness of the game
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.88,0:20:44.18,Default,,0,0,0,,you have to stick your hand into the terrifying deeps
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.15,0:21:15.78,Default,,0,0,0,,It... passed
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.78,0:21:19.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Afterwards, all Hiroyuki must do is deal in with his 5 Sou
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.25,0:21:25.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Judging merely by that Red Dragon
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.95,0:21:30.61,Default,,0,0,0,,he ought not be discarding dora which are likely to complete Soga's Chinisou
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.61,0:21:33.98,Default,,0,0,0,,He's in tenpai for a huge hand
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.85,0:21:41.71,Default,,0,0,0,,A SanAnKou?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.05,0:21:47.81,Default,,0,0,0,,If I leave it be for one turn
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.81,0:21:51.45,Default,,0,0,0,,and the kid deals into it, it's over
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.91,0:22:02.78,Default,,0,0,0,,One moment now
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.58,0:22:09.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Kan
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.11,0:22:32.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Kan!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.50,0:22:48.80,Default,,0,0,0,,When Harada flipped those two Dora indicators
Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:00.00,Default,,0,0,0,,he swapped in tiles he had, giving Dora to Ten
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.78,0:23:00.00,Default,,0,0,0,,With his hidden Red Dragon Kan, it's a SanBaiMan hand
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.16,0:23:05.14,Default,,0,0,0,,As the point value is so high, he can't deal into it
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.06,0:23:14.49,Default,,0,0,0,,We survived
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.53,0:23:18.53,Default,,0,0,0,,If the kid were to deal into that
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.53,0:23:20.53,Default,,0,0,0,,he'd only have 1000 points left
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.53,0:23:23.23,Default,,0,0,0,,pretty much an act of suicide
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.23,0:23:26.16,Default,,0,0,0,,and thus Ten's SanAnKou is no more
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.13,0:23:30.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Afterwards Soga will collect a 4 Sou
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.76,0:23:33.26,Default,,0,0,0,,or I'll complete my hand and knock you out
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.26,0:23:35.26,Default,,0,0,0,,no problem
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.44,0:23:53.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on, kid. I took this hand last turn
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.32,0:24:23.76,Default,,0,0,0,,that's crazy!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.76,0:24:26.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, Ten won't even accept that direct hit
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.39,0:24:32.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that the way it is?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.86,0:24:35.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, if that's your gut feeling
Dialogue: 0,0:24:35.26,0:24:37.26,Default,,0,0,0,,it's okay then
Dialogue: 0,0:24:37.26,0:24:39.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll take it
Dialogue: 0,0:24:51.09,0:24:54.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Ron
Dialogue: 0,0:24:57.66,0:24:59.34,Default,,0,0,0,,24,000 points
Dialogue: 0,0:24:59.34,0:25:03.42,Default,,0,0,0,,and SanAnKou has been cleared
